[l] Der Ex-Chef von Citigroup findet heute, dass man grosse Banken zerschlagen muss und wieder eine Trennung zwischen Banking und Investment Banking einfuehren muss. Das gab es frueher, das Gesetz hiess Glass-Steagall Act.Now retired, Mr Reed firmly believes that the business logic behind the transaction was flawed, and that the old Glass-Steagall division should be reinstated. Mr Reed first expressed this view soon after the crisis erupted. Last year Sandy Weill, the other main architect of the Citicorp-Travelers deal, changed his position to support breaking up the banks.Falls euch die FT-Paywall nicht reinlaesst: Huffington Post dazu.
